<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-05-17T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-05-17T16:00:00-05:00" n="91" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d91">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 763.72/4781c</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Minister in Denmark</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_EMF1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Egan</hi></persName>)<note n="2" xml:id="d91fn2">The same telegram was sent May 17 to the
                                    Minister in Switzerland (No. 582) and the Chargé in the
                                    Netherlands (No. 521).</note>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-05-17T16:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">May 17, 1917, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>354. In scanning German press, please watch for comment indicating
                                German jubilation or satisfaction over what they may take to be
                                America’s dilatory start in the war.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>